Processes:-  when you launch an App,  it Converts to Processes.

to list all running processes
$ ls proc

to List PID

if you know the PID and want to know whose use this PID (want to know the application o Service)
1- PID ➡️ ,  app ❌   
$ top -p PID    =>  top -p 1548

2- app ➡️ ,  PID ❌
$ pgrep app/service  => pgrep  firefox                   => Just  Print the "Parent PID"   (Lowest PID)
$ pidof app/service                                      => List All processes Related to this app/service

3- PID ❌ ,  app ❌
$ pstree -p    (-p  to print the PID)  pstree will just list the processes as a tree but without  printing the PID
$ ps  -aux
$ top


The "State" Of Broken process will be "R"  and use high Resources


------------------------------ Signals  -----------------------------

$ man 7 signal        

1-   1  => Reload / Reread 

2-   9  => force Terminate

3-   15 =>  Clean Terminate

----------------------------------   Stop Process  -------------------------------
$ kill     -singal  PID          => kill -9  1519

$ pkill   -signal  PID           => pkill  -15  fire        (pkill  =>  kill pattern,  if you type  "fire" then will  terminate    firewall,  firefox,  firezilla ....)

$ killall -signal  FullAppName   => killall -9 firefox        (killall will Close the Firefox app not just the broken or unwanted process and will terminate it for  all  Users if you r Admin) 





Multiuser    =>  the System Contain Multi Account/Users ,   and Many Users can Login at the same Time 
